news.title: TARC expects Rs 2,000 crore revenue from next phase of its two projects
news.para: The developer has reported pre-sales of Rs 1,165 crore, during Q3FY25 taking the pre-sale to Rs 2,487 crore in the first nine months of FY2025, nearly six-fold year-on-year increase.

news.title: Akzo Nobel NV to sell powder coating business for Rs 2,073 crore
news.para: The binding offer also includes sale and transfer of the intellectual property for the decorative paints business by Akzo Nobel Coatings International B.V. to Akzo Nobel India.

news.title: New initiative to provide e-katha launched in Mandya
news.para: MLA P Ravi Kumar Ganiga launched the drive on Monday and urged residents within Mandya city limits to take full advantage of the campaign.

news.title: Land records must reflect court orders to prevent illegal deals: Karnataka HC
news.para: "Revenue authorities, as custodians of land records, are duty-bound to comply with orders of the civil court and ensure that rights declared by judicial forums are given full effect," Justice Sachin Shankar Magadum observed in his order while allowing the petition filed by one Suvarna.

news.title: YEIDA to acquire more land near Jewar Airport
news.para: The state is already in the process of executing several projects in the region, including a film city, a medical device park, a logistics park and a data centre park.

news.title: Three sports city projects in Noida face CBI, ED probes
news.para: A division bench of justices Mahesh Chandra Tripathi and Prashant Kumar issued 10 separate judgments covering the three projects on Monday.

news.title: China: Shimao Group secures creditor backing for $11 billion offshore debt revamp
news.para: Sunac China became the first troubled Chinese property developer to successfully reduce its onshore debt earlier this year, while CIFI Holdings has reached an agreement with a key group of bondholders on an offshore debt restructuring plan.

news.title: Delhi civic body announces house-tax waiver for residents
news.para: ​The announcement was made at a press conference here on Monday by MCD Mayor Mahesh Khichi, Deputy Mayor Ravinder Bhardwaj, Leader of the House Mukesh Goel and senior Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) leader and Rajya Sabha MP Sanjay Singh.

news.title: Apollo Global Management to buy Bridge Investment for $1.5 billion
news.para: Bridge stockholders and unit holders of its subsidiary will each receive 0.07081 shares of Apollo stock for every share they hold, with each share valued at $11.50, the companies said on Monday.

news.title: MNCs rent nearly 51 lakh sq ft office space in last two years to set up GCCs in Delhi-NCR: Anarock
news.para: ​"In Delhi-NCR, GCCs leased 5.09 million (50.9 lakh) sq ft gross office space in last two years - of which nearly 2.5 million sq ft in 2023 and 2.59 million sq ft in 2024, thereby increasing by 4 per cent on yearly basis," real estate consultant Anarock said.

news.title: Punjab assembly committee recommends hike in financial assistance under PMAY-G
news.para: ​Under the Pradhan Mantri Gramin Awas Yojana, a financial assistance of Rs 1.20 lakh is given to eligible beneficiaries for the construction of a house by the Centre. The assistance is paid in three instalments.

news.title: Notandas Realty expands into Juhu with Notan DC project
news.para: Located on Juhu’s 10th Road, the existing property will embody elegance, sophistication, and modernity. ‘We are thrilled to set a new standard for luxury living in Mumbai,’ said Mr Harsh Jagwani, Managing Director of Notandas Realty.

news.title: Asian Paints, JSW Steel, others had pledged promoter holdings over 5% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Kotak Equities analysed the pledged shareholdings of BSE-500 companies and found that the promoters of 69 companies have pledged a part of their stake in respective companies as on December 31, 2024 ended quarter.

news.title: Activists question Vasai Virar civic body's double standards on illegal buildings
news.para: Hendriques added that he has submitted a list of over 30 dhabas and eateries that dot NH48 to VVCMC, but it has not acted yet. More shocking, he said, was the fire brigade's clearance to the eateries.

news.title: Kalaburagi gets Karnataka's government nod for taller housing developments
news.para: The state govt's approval on Feb 18 for increasing building height limits addresses a long-standing request from city residents.

news.title: Adani Group to invest Rs 1.1 lakh crore across multiple sectors in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: The Group has already invested over Rs 50,000 crore in Madhya Pradesh across energy, infrastructure, manufacturing, logistics and agri-business, generating more than 25,000 jobs.

news.title: Belagavi civic body to conduct e-khata mela on February 24
news.para: ​Accordingly, it is intended to issue e-Khata to all properties pending within the jurisdiction of urban local bodies in the state within three months. The minimum required documents should be submitted to obtain A and B accounts of the properties.

news.title: Kerala: Of nine lakh documents registered yearly, only 500 done independently
news.para: Since the introduction of the facility on March 1, 2016, through a notification by the inspector general of registrations, only 4,430 documents have been prepared and registered by citizens without the assistance of document writers or advocates.

news.title: Noida authority to e-auction industry plots under new policy soon
news.para: Spread across sectors 7, 8, 10, 62, 80, and 164, these plots will have a total area of around 60,000sqm. Authority officials confirmed that the scheme would be launched anytime soon as most administrative preparations were already complete.

news.title: Alt plans to raise Rs 2,800 crore in 2025
news.para: Following SEBI's SM REIT regulations in 2024, Property Share became the first to secure an SM REIT license in Aug 2024 and listed a Rs 353 crore asset in Dec, marking India's first listed SM REIT.
